# BROWSER-notifications.md - Dev.to Notification & Reply Patterns

## SS 1: Batch Extract Notifications

Open `https://dev.to/notifications/comments` first.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/navigate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"url":"https://dev.to/notifications/comments"}' 2>&1
```

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); const notifications = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('div.crayons-card.notification')); const unreplied = notifications.filter(n => !n.innerHTML.includes('>Replied<')); return { total: notifications.length, count: unreplied.length, items: unreplied.slice(0, 5).map(notif => { const allLinks = Array.from(notif.querySelectorAll('a')); const commentLink = allLinks.find(a => a.href.includes('/comment/') && !a.href.includes('/{{handle}}/comment/')); return { username: notif.innerText.split(String.fromCharCode(10))[0].split(' ')[0], commentUrl: commentLink ? commentLink.href : '' }; }).filter(n => n.commentUrl) }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

🚨 **IMPORTANT:** Only `commentUrl` and `username` are returned. `articleUrl` is NOT needed — the comment page has all context.

