## SS 2: Reply to Comment (4 steps total)

### Step 1: Navigate to commentUrl

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/navigate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"url":"COMMENT_URL"}' 2>&1
```

### Step 2: Context check + click Reply (ONE async evaluate with 3s embedded wait):
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); const alreadyReplied = document.querySelectorAll('#comment-trees-container a[href*=\"/{{handle}}\"]').length > 0; if (alreadyReplied) return { alreadyReplied: true }; var targetComment = document.querySelector('.comment__body'); if (targetComment) { var depth = 0; var el = targetComment.closest('[data-comment-id]'); if (el) { el = el.parentElement; while (el) { if (el.hasAttribute('data-comment-id')) depth++; el = el.parentElement; } } if (depth >= 3) return { skipped: true, reason: 'too_deep', depth: depth }; } const repliesForLink = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('a')).find(a => a.innerText.startsWith('Replies for:')); const comment = document.querySelector('.comment__body'); const replyBtn = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')).find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Reply'); if (replyBtn) replyBtn.click(); return { alreadyReplied: false, parentContext: repliesForLink ? repliesForLink.innerText.slice(0, 200) : null, replyText: comment ? comment.innerText.slice(0, 300) : null, replyClicked: !!replyBtn }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

If `alreadyReplied: true` -> skip. If `replyClicked: false` -> skip.

### Step 3: Type reply (1.5s embedded wait):
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500)); const textarea = document.querySelector('textarea[placeholder=\"Reply...\"]'); if (!textarea) return {error: 'no textarea'}; textarea.click(); textarea.focus(); textarea.value = REPLY_TEXT_HERE; textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', {bubbles: true})); textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', {bubbles: true})); return {typed: true, length: textarea.value.length}; }"}
ENDJSON
```

### Step 4: Submit + verify (0.5s + 3s embedded waits):
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); const submitBtn = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')).find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Submit'); if (!submitBtn) return {error: 'no submit button'}; submitBtn.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); return { verified: document.querySelectorAll('#comment-trees-container a[href*=\"/{{handle}}\"]').length > 0 }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

If `verified: false` -> retry step 4 once. Still false -> don't log, retry next heartbeat.

🚨 **NEVER navigate to the full article just to read context.** The comment URL page has all context.
